            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47175",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Could you provide some sample code showing how you're using Zend_Session_SaveHandler_DbTable, how you handle the exception, and some information on the exception that was thrown?  (esp: the class name and stack trace)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-06-13T14:36:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-06-13T14:36:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47276",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tbeijen",
                        "name": "tbeijen",
                        "displayName": "Tibo Beijen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "We're running into the same issue.\r\nIt's just a fatal error, there's no exception.\r\nWe're using Zend Framework 1.9.7\r\n\r\nError occurs on a PHP 5.3.3 server. Same code runs fine on a PHP 5.3.6 server\r\n\r\nError log:\r\n{code}\r\n[27-Jun-2011 11:15:25] PHP Fatal error:  Undefined class constant 'PRIMARY_TYPE_NUM' in \/home\/........\/libraries\/Zend\/1.9.7\/Zend\/Session\/SaveHandler\/DbTable.php on line 522\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nServer having fatal error:\r\n{code}\r\nPHP 5.3.3 (cli) (built: Aug  7 2010 14:49:50)\r\nCopyright (c) 1997-2010 The PHP Group\r\nZend Engine v2.3.0, Copyright (c) 1998-2010 Zend Technologies\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nServer running fine:\r\n{code}\r\nPHP 5.3.6 (cli) (built: Mar 19 2011 07:44:03)\r\nCopyright (c) 1997-2011 The PHP Group\r\nZend Engine v2.3.0, Copyright (c) 1998-2011 Zend Technologies\r\n    with the ionCube PHP Loader v4.0.9, Copyright (c) 2002-2011, by ionCube Ltd., and\r\n    with Xdebug v2.1.0, Copyright (c) 2002-2010, by Derick Rethans\r\n{code}\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tbeijen",
                        "name": "tbeijen",
                        "displayName": "Tibo Beijen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-06-27T09:31:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-06-27T09:31:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47296",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Tibo: Can you try it on PHP 5.3.3 with the latest ZF release? (or better yet, against SVN trunk)\r\n\r\nI can't reproduce the issue against trunk on my dev machine:\r\n{code}\r\nPHP 5.3.3 (cli) (built: Jan 28 2011 14:53:13)\r\nCopyright (c) 1997-2010 The PHP Group\r\nZend Engine v2.3.0, Copyright (c) 1998-2010 Zend Technologies\r\n    with the ionCube PHP Loader v4.0.5, Copyright (c) 2002-2011, by ionCube Ltd., and\r\n    with Xdebug v2.1.0, Copyright (c) 2002-2010, by Derick Rethans\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-06-28T16:59:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-06-28T17:00:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47397",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jaymecd",
                        "name": "jaymecd",
                        "displayName": "Nikolai Zujev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI've discovered this issue few mins ago and found solution. checked with PHP 5.3.3 and ZF 1.11.7 & 1.11.8\r\n\r\nHow to reproduce:\r\n - use DbTable handler\r\n - trigger fatal error\r\n - see error message describer above\r\n\r\nAfter debugging noticed that object is already destroyed and it does not have any static properties.\r\n{code:title=Zend\/Session\/SaveHandler\/DbTable.php} \r\nprotected function _getPrimary($id, $type = null)\r\n{\r\n    $refl = new ReflectionClass($this);\r\n\r\n    error_log('CHECK: '.print_r($refl->getConstants(),1));\r\n\r\n    ... rest code ...\r\n}\r\n{code} \r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\n[08-Jul-2011 11:38:31] PHP Fatal error:  xxx in \/path\/app\/module\/default\/action\/IndexController.php on line 26\r\n[08-Jul-2011 11:38:31] PHP Stack trace: [clipped]\r\n[08-Jul-2011 11:38:31] CHECK: Array()\r\n[08-Jul-2011 11:38:31] PHP Fatal error:  Undefined class constant 'PRIMARY_TYPE_NUM' in \/path\/lib\/Zend\/Session\/SaveHandler\/DbTable.php on line 525\r\n[08-Jul-2011 11:38:31] PHP Stack trace: [clipped]\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nWorkaround is taken from php.net manual.\r\n\r\nPay attention to this note:\r\n{panel:title=http:\/\/www.php.net\/manual\/en\/function.session-set-save-handler.php}\r\nAs of PHP 5.0.5 the write and close handlers are called after object destruction and therefore cannot use objects or throw exceptions. The object destructors can however use sessions.\r\n{panel}\r\n\r\nBy setting shutdown callback as: *register_shutdown_function('session_write_close');*\r\nin the entry point (index.php) you avoid this issue.\r\n\r\nHave a nice day,\r\nNick",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jaymecd",
                        "name": "jaymecd",
                        "displayName": "Nikolai Zujev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-08T12:14:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-08T12:14:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47403",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jaymecd",
                        "name": "jaymecd",
                        "displayName": "Nikolai Zujev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "UPD. forgot to mention - front controller should be set to throw exceptions, aka in development mode.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jaymecd",
                        "name": "jaymecd",
                        "displayName": "Nikolai Zujev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-08T20:38:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-08T20:38:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49858",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=valugi",
                        "name": "valugi",
                        "displayName": "elzo valugi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I get the same errror. This is quite strange as the user has SELECT rights.\r\n\r\nFatal error: Uncaught exception 'PDOException' with message 'SQLSTATE[42000]: Syntax error or access violation: 1142 SELECT command denied to user 'green'@'localhost' for table 'application__users'' in \/var\/opt\/ZendFramework\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Db\/Statement\/Pdo.php:228 \r\n\r\nStack trace: #0 \/var\/opt\/ZendFramework\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Db\/Statement\/Pdo.php(228): PDOStatement->execute(Array) #1 \/var\/opt\/ZendFramework\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Db\/Statement.php(300): Zend_Db_Statement_Pdo->_execute(Array) #2 \/var\/opt\/ZendFramework\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Abstract.php(479): Zend_Db_Statement->execute(Array) #3 \/var\/opt\/ZendFramework\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Pdo\/Abstract.php(238): Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract->query('DESCRIBE `mydb...', Array) #4 \/var\/opt\/ZendFramework\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Pdo\/Mysql.php(169): Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Abstract->query('DESCRIBE `mydb...') #5 \/var\/opt\/ZendFramework\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Db\/Table\/Abstract.php(835): Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Mysql->describeTable('application__us...', 'mydb') #6 \/var\/opt\/ZendFra in \/var\/opt\/ZendFramework\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Controller\/Plugin\/Broker.php on line 312 Fatal error: Undefined class constant 'PRIMARY_TYPE_NUM' in \/var\/opt\/ZendFramework\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Session\/SaveHandler\/DbTable.php on line 522",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=valugi",
                        "name": "valugi",
